Here‚Äôs a breakdown of **SAP Modules sector-wise**, highlighting **5 major modules** relevant to **specific industries or business functions**:

---

## üîπ **SAP Modules ‚Äî Sector-Wise Breakdown (Top 5)**

| **Sector**                     | **SAP Module**    | **Full Form**                                              | **Purpose**                                                          |
| ------------------------------ | ----------------- | ---------------------------------------------------------- | -------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| **Manufacturing / Production** | **SAP PP**        | **Production Planning**                                    | Manages production schedules, shop floor control, material planning. |
| **Finance / Accounting**       | **SAP FI**        | **Financial Accounting**                                   | Handles financial reporting, ledgers, accounts receivable/payable.   |
| **Human Resources**            | **SAP HCM / HXM** | **Human Capital Management** / Human Experience Management | Manages payroll, employee records, time management.                  |
| **Sales & Distribution**       | **SAP SD**        | **Sales and Distribution**                                 | Manages order processing, shipping, billing, customer data.          |
| **Supply Chain / Inventory**   | **SAP MM**        | **Materials Management**                                   | Handles procurement, inventory, material master data.                |

---

## ‚úÖ **Bonus Sector-Wise Mapping**

| **Sector / Industry**     | **Relevant SAP Modules**                                                   |
| ------------------------- | -------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| **Retail & FMCG**         | SAP SD, SAP MM, SAP CRM, SAP IS-Retail                                     |
| **Healthcare**            | SAP IS-H (Industry Solution ‚Äì Healthcare), SAP FI, SAP HCM                 |
| **Banking & Finance**     | SAP FI, SAP CO, SAP TRM (Treasury), SAP FS (Financial Services)            |
| **Logistics / SCM**       | SAP MM, SAP WM (Warehouse Mgmt), SAP EWM (Extended WM), SAP TM (Transport) |
| **Oil & Gas / Utilities** | SAP IS-Oil, SAP PM (Plant Maintenance), SAP PS (Project Systems)           |

